ME VS 2023 

In 2023 it was more than I that had an uphill battle generating the amount of work I’ve done over the year… 
I’ve put out projects of mass in very little time all under 28 hrs or less in actual tattooing for each and every one of these projects… it started off with a bang and ended with a Boom… The year was filled with growth, lesson and appreciation… The loss of our Brother @v_ngata was the absolute low of my entire year to having to return to work with him no longer by my side was an absolute blow to me and the brothers at XODUS… But We’ve managed to band together and work harder for brother Vili because thats what he’d expect from us and nothing less… But this uphill battle was done and won with the effort and patience of my clientele to push thru those hrs and days to obtain such pieces…. Here’s to y’all you’ve earned it… much love and respect for yall… 
Although not everyone made my 9 but everyone one of yall deserve it in every way… I used some of my top pieces done and ones that I felt had mass amounts of ink done as well as the ones that had a hand in pushing me as an artist… Believe me they had push but some had pressure and steady pressure is what we on… My own apprentice didn’t make the cut and he got double sleeves done on him in a matter of 40 hrs or less… I just didn’t have a pic of him with both arms fresh… So here’s to you my loyal clientele, my friends, my family and my fans… yall the reason why I am here and why I stay in the game we love most… 
Thank You
